hey <@U05ASNPAB3Q> you can do this if you're embedding your form. you'll want to use the onFormSubmitted callback in the hbspt.forms.create() method. Here's an example of how you can append the email from the submitted form to the redirect URL:

```hbspt.forms.create({
  portalId: '',
  formId: '',
  onFormSubmitted: function ($form, data) {
    // Get the email from the submitted data
    var email = data.submissionValues.email;

    // Define your custom redirect URL with the form email appended
    var redirectUrl = '<https://www.samplepage.com/thank-you?email=>' + encodeURIComponent(email);

    // Redirect the user to the custom URL
    window.location = redirectUrl;
  },
});```
This should work in both normal and incognito browsing modes. Make sure you replace the empty strings in the portalId and formId properties with your actual Portal ID and Form ID.
